    type: 2}
  <SpawnTable>k__BackingField: 1
  <BestiaryNodeText>k__BackingField: 'The Tickle Monster


    Sigurd''s danger level:
    -F%


    Scientific name: SCP-999


    When I saw this thing I thought it was
    a Hygrodere, but after closer inspection, it moves and behaves a lot differently.
    It seems to have an affinity to humans. Touching it made me feel relaxed, like
    all my fear just melted away. It followed us around and gave us hugs to calm
    us down. Richard got shot by a turret while we were exploring and the thing jumped
    in front of the turret fire! It tackled Richard and his wounds were no longer
    there. I wonder if we could bottle this stuff up and use it for healing injuries,
    it''d be a lot better than any modern medicine for sure.



    After having
    it around for a while we did learn that this little guy also likes healing other
    creatures, so we had to drag him away if we wanted to get rid of them.



    Many
    people might have many different name for this little guy, but the only good
    name i could give him was "friend" -Sigurd'
  <BestiaryWordOverride>k__BackingField: SCP-999
